# AfricGraph Frontend Design Rules

## Visual Style Guidelines

- Prefer custom CSS-in-JS or advanced Tailwind for complex visual effects (e.g., glow, glass).
- Never use default 'shadcn/ui' themes; always customize the design tokens to be dark/technical.
- Use `framer-motion` for all state-based layout transitions.

## Design Aesthetic: "High-Tech Data Observatory"

### Color Palette
- Background: Deep navy/midnight (#030712 or #0A0F1E)
- Glass panels: backdrop-blur-md with 1px semi-transparent borders
- Accent colors: Neons, Cyans, Deep Darks

### Typography
- Data values: Roboto Mono or JetBrains Mono (monospaced)
- Headers: Clean technical sans-serif (Inter or Roboto Mono)

### Components
- NO standard white/light grey cards
- NO Lucide/FontAwesome generic icons (use geometric shapes or SVG paths)
- NO generic Tailwind "rounded-lg" borders
- NO basic 2D charts

### 3D Graph (react-force-graph-3d)
- Nodes: Glowing spheres (color intensity = Risk Level)
- Relationships: Thin, animated "data filaments"
- High-risk nodes: Outer "warning" pulse effect

### Micro-interactions
- Subtle "scan-line" overlay effect on dashboard
- framer-motion for "staggered" entry animations
- Custom SVG "Ring" gauge for risk scores

### Risk Visualization
- Use "Radar" charts and "Liquid Fill" gauges
- NOT standard bar charts
